definitions: (especially of a country) almost or entirely surrounded by land; having no coastline or seaport

examples.text: a midget state landlocked in the mountains

shortDefinitions: (of country or region) almost or entirely surrounded by land

definitions: (of a lake) enclosed by land and having no navigable route to the sea
shortDefinitions: (of lake or harbour) enclosed by land and having no navigable route to sea

definitions: (of a fish, especially a North American salmon) cut off from the sea in the past and now confined to fresh water
shortDefinitions: (of fish) cut off from sea in past and now confined to fresh water
